// Pasting HTML-literal angle brackets into an editor must not crash the
// tokenizer/rule loop, and must not generate an unexpected finding. The
// popover renderer layer is where the <em>-wrapped explain template is
// produced — rule.explain() calls escapeHtml on every interpolated token,
// and spell-check.js's showPopover escapeHtml/escapeAttr wraps original +
// suggestion display. This fixture confirms the core + rule surface stays
// network-silent and crash-free on angle-bracket input. Full XSS assertion
